type="local"
addr="jms-00IS">matrices</fr:link> and finite <fr:link
href="jms-00I7.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00I7">relations</fr:link> (<fr:ref
addr="jms-00J1"
href="jms-00J1.xml"></fr:ref>, <fr:ref
addr="jms-00IX"
href="jms-00IX.xml"
taxon="Lemma"></fr:ref>), <fr:link
href="jms-00IV.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00IV">matrix products</fr:link> of boolean <fr:link
href="jms-00IS.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00IS">matrices</fr:link> correspond to <fr:link
href="jms-00IN.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00IN">relational composites</fr:link>. In particular, given <fr:tex>M \in \mathrm {Mat}_{ \mathbb {B} } { \mathopen {} \left ( l , m \right ) \mathclose {}}</fr:tex> and <fr:tex>N \in \mathrm {Mat}_{ \mathbb {B} } { \mathopen {} \left ( m , n \right ) \mathclose {}}</fr:tex>, we have:</fr:p><fr:tex
display="block">   \operatorname { \underline {rel}} _ \mathbb {B} { \mathopen {} \left ( N \cdot  M \right ) \mathclose {}}  =  \operatorname { \underline {rel}} _ \mathbb {B}  N \circ   \operatorname { \underline {rel}} _ \mathbb {B}  M </fr:tex>
 
   
